latestPosts.caption:
Stop getting a faded haircut 💇🏻‍♂️ (Details ⬇️)
.
1. Prep the Hair,Spray hair with water,Comb to remove tangles.
2. Section the Hair,Separate into: top, sides, and back (use clips if needed).
3. Cut the Top. Start at the front top. Use fingers to hold a section.
Cut to desired length (3–5 inches).
Work back in rows, using the first cut as a guide.
4. Trim the Sides & Blend.
Use clippers (guard no. 4/6) or scissors over comb.
Blend sides into the top with vertical cutting.
5. Taper the Back
Use scissors to trim from top to neckline.

6. Add Texture (Optional)
Use thinning shears or point cut to add movement.
7. Clean Edges & Style
Trim around ears and neckline.
Style with matte cream or pomade.
.
Pro tip: get a better barber 🥰
.
